snippet.textDisplay:
Kirby should be looked at from the angle of being a tool that can be directed by others, because that's all he has ever been. No one has yet had the audacity to try and pin Kirby down, to keep Kirby from being controlled by someone else, because of Kirby's strong individual willpower and terrifyingly strong powers. But when it becomes necessary, people can point Kirby in the right direction. King Dedede, a frequent antagonist in the series, literally grabs Kirby and throws them at the final boss of a game (a final boss who, throughout the game, had been themselves manipulating Kirby for personal gain).

Kirby is science. A tool that can be wielded for good or for evil, but cannot be controlled by any one man. Which is capable of studying and copying things from the world around it and re purposing them. It seems nice at first, is good at putting on a friendly face (it looks like a good thing most of the time) but when you scrutinize it, you realize that if left unchecked it is capable of great destruction.
Science was used to make light bulbs. Computers. Radios. Smart phones. Vaccines.
Science discovered nuclear power. It also created the atom bomb.
Some theorize that science could lead us to a singularity, an infinitely growing intelligence capable of altering the entire universe to suit whatever purpose it winds up choosing. But we haven't made the singularity yet, and we don't know for sure if it ever will actually happen.

Science is also responsible for video games. Everybody loves video games!

KIRBY IS A METAPHOR FOR SCIENCE.

snippet.textDisplay: Ok so, while I thought the video was certainly funny and well made, you are missing some key facts about Kirby. In the Anime (that you mentioned to exist and that you trusted anime) it blatantly shows that Kirby is a very young star warrior from the stars (owning up to his Japanese name Hoshi no Kirby or Kirby of the Stars). Meta Knight actually explains his origins in an episode and talks about the star warriors’ fights against evil entities like Nightmare in Kirby’s Adventure (the base game that inspires a large portion of the Anime). If you played the most recent entry, it somewhat hints (at least it seems like it does) that Kirby is actually made from dark matter (one of Kirby’s strongest and craziest looking foes). It hints this by showing that the core of the enemy you showed that he goes up against as a final boss in the most recent entry, Kirby Star Allies, makes its figure into both the monikers of Dark Matter and Kirby. In any case, while his backstory, chemical makeup and specific personality aren’t all too easy to understand, you just need to look into it a bit more to understand it better. As someone who owns and has completed every Kirby game, including the side games like Kirby Air Ride, I am a big fan of the Kirby franchise and the fact that you really don’t need to know much else besides “Kirby is a cute dude with awesome powers that they use to destroy evil”. Its a nice break from games with many characters with lives, backstory, etc.. Honestly, either you didn’t do your homework like you said, or you just wanted to put this together to be funny. I’m going to guess that it’s the latter because the joke you made at the end about Diddy’s Rocketbarrels and Peanut Popguns (which is their proper names) from DK 64 is so easy to lookup that it was kind of a jarring joke for me. Diddy’s Rocketbarrels we’re made by Cranky Kong and run on Crystal Coconuts and his Peanut Popguns were made by Funky Kong and shoot peanuts as ammo (which were going to be real dual wielded pistols but were changed by Nintendo during development for obvious reasons). Anyway, I really like the videos, I’m inferring that you have chosen to see Kirby this way as a joke and that’s cool honestly. Though I doubt they will actually be reading this.

snippet.textDisplay:
Kirby embodies the heat death of the universe. The last vestige of anthropomorphized consciousness, consuming the last tree of the Easter Island which is all existence.

Will a future galactic civilization construct a reflective sphere encapsulating a black hole and riding out eternity by suckling away at Hawking radiation and cheating net energy gains by skipping waves off the event horizon? Kirby can only surpass the end of all things if Kirby encounters such a construction that has already been built.

And thus Kirby only possesses infinite power as a foil to existing creation... One might conclude this perfectly suits Kirby's true nature as the ultimate devourer, the Time Ender.

One cannot defeat Kirby, only surrender. Which is why Kirby is shaped like a friend. Because at the end of the universe, with nothing left to gain or give, you'll welcome demise of all things like a friend.

Accounting that all things ever created can and will be consumed... Kirby is the continual final form in the making. A circle with a smile.

The initial folly BDG makes here is to falsely dichotomize an infinitely faceted construction... The irony and foreshadowing of the conclusion is hinted at as humanity's hubris... If the game is Texas hold em, you can't win by building a house of cards. But can you imagine watching WPT where a player stops playing the game and just starts building a house?

That's where Kirby comes in... Sucks the whole casino up... The entire Vegas strip up... And in that finite moment you wonder if Kirby is even going to bother with Fremont... But no such consideration is ever made, and before you know it, all of White Sands, Groom Lake and the Alamogordo Landfill are consumed, and Kirby is now the Mojave. Good job, Kirby.

snippet.textDisplay:
I think Kirby is the ultimate checks and balance system. He's only powerful when need be, he's only aggressive with attacked or bothered, he's only motivated when pushed to be by an external, powerful force. Steal his food, he beats you up and steals your food. Hurt his friends, he hurts yours. Disturb his sleep time, he destroys your every last dream. He exists purely to save reality from itself, he's the self-healing agent of all that is, almost like a universe's immune system.

His infinite power is limited only by the occasion and environment he exists in. He cant even attack reliably without something else trying to stop or harm him. His only attacks without spitting up an object are blowing a puff of air and sliding on the ground, the latter of which doesnt even hurt enemies, just breaks blocks. His every skill, every power and ability are externally-based, be they copied, wielded or obtained as a gift.

He alone is just a star child, adrift in his base needs until he is kick-started into action. Whether the trigger is stolen food, a hurt ally or the prevention of sleep, Kirby is only dangerous when not left alone. If he was a hulking, all knowing mass or entity, he'd have to pick and choose when to act. He's an unalligned agent ready to spring into action at the toss of a hat, but his innocent, friendly and unassuming appearance are just tools to further his power and potential.

What he cannot do or where he cannot go, his friends aid him. Enemies do not cower or plan around him because if they did, he wouldn't be able to know they need to be stopped. It's hard to even know about him because he is just so simple and potently brutal in his fighting, theres hardly any foe he faces who doesnt consistently die in the end, save for those like Meta Knight and King Dedede, probably only spared because they're Kirby's friends, even if they dont like it or wanna be.

Kirby is friend-shaped, and for your protection, you'd best be his friend. * ★Poyo!★ *

snippet.textDisplay:
Kirby is acually God/Absolute from a hegelian perspective, let me explain point for point.

1.Kirbys core characteristics are simpicity and power: Both are true for God as the underlying unity for everything. But because he is also the principle of unity he can not be complex, and if so only as a part of a higher order unity, here unity is equal to simplicity. Even more so because for Hegel God is the thing which desolves all complexity and duality in a new unity which encompasses the complexity before it.
2.Kirby cares only about sleeping and eating: For Hegel God creates, to become selfcouncess, the world so that in the world becoming and beeing at the same time identical with him he can think about himself. We as humans for example need to take a step back from the direkt day to day beeing to reflect about ourselves. God does the same only that his step back ist the creation and existence of the world. What has this to do with only eating and sleeping? simple, When Kirby eats he takes it in and it becomes part of him, more so he becomes part of it too. This is exactly the nature of reflection for God. He takes the part of him that he reflects upon and makes it part of his identity. The thing that gets back to the unity of god becomes part of Him and God becomes part of it. This is also an active process by god, we can of course not see it because we are this process and the material at the same time. And Sleeping? Simple, sleeping is remaining by one self, without anything else, just beeing. The same is true for God because for Hegel he is active unto his road to councessnes but at the same time always remains by himself.

3.Kirby destroys that which he consumes: From what we already established, everything in existence is created from God to be later on reincorporated into himself. So when kirby consumes something it simply is reincorpareted into him, he was allready what he consumed before he consumed it.
4.Kirby can speak a language but cannot understand telephones: Simple, Language or rather the instinct to language is born within us, created and needed by God. So he can understand it. But a Telephone only makes sense from a human perspective.And because God is the process of overcomming any special perspective, as long as the human perspective is not overcome he will not understand it. It was created by a part of himself he doesnt understand yet.

5. Kirby can use Mechas: One would assume that from the last point kirby also cant use technology in general. But this isnt true. Mechas and other technology doesnt need a subjective human perspective to make any sense. A robo warrior makes perfekt sense in the battle of the fittest in nature. So nothing stops god from using it, He also doesnt need to know how they work, because he created the matter they are made from so he simply controlls that.
6.Kirbys Origins are vague, of course they are God is uncreated, he doesnt have an Origin.
7. Kirby posses unlimited Power: Just like God.

8.Kirby is shaped like a Friend: For Hegel the purpose of the Human is to create the final reconciliation, the final self realization of God. So it makes only sense that god as the point unto which this goal is directed appears as something pleasent, as something which is easily approached, as a friend.
8.Kirby battles cosmic horros: If god incarnates into the process which he created to become self ware fully, of course he will battle that which doesnt want to archieve a higher plane of realization, that which goes against the cosmic order, and which is therefore a cosmic horror. But because God knows that this process is natural he doesnt harbor any bad feelings.

9.Kirby doesnt have emotional intelligence: Of course Not because to have emotionens you need differentiation you need to make differences between happy and sad, between i and them etc.. God Telos his goal is to overcome such dualities, so he doesnt have emotions.
One might now ask but why should god incarnate in this world. simple because he also needs to get beyond the difference between beeing beyond and within the world. And one can even say that this interpretation is true whatever the author had in mind because god in this idea works through us as tools who dont yet realizie it all. And the Lawyer thing. Kirby named after a lawyer who defended rights. That is obvious. Im sorry for my bad english im german, also i dont know how the english translate some words from hegel but i hope it still makes sense. So as a final word. May Kirby forgive our Sins and may we pray to be gifted the realization about his true nature.

snippet.textDisplay:
Kirby is entropy.
He is all powerful because in the end he will consomme all things, the various eldritch entities hate and fear him, because for all their power, they are nothing before the ravages of time. Yet Kirby is not cruel nor malicious, for what dose he have to fear from us? Do you fear any given fly? And do you suppose that your actions are even remotely fathomable to such a beast? He is also content, as being entropy he his aware and accepting of his own mortality, and as such feels no need to exert or display his power, least of all to lowly being such as us. While he can manipulate technology he is most likely simply unaware of why what he dose works, merely that they do. Finally he accepts all of us, no matter our beliefs or actions, in the end we will all fade into dust, into Kirby, he knows this, and he embraces us as a friend.
